<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.278397>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A. Female Gekko japonicus (G. japonicus group), photo by J. Boone; B. Male G. hokouensis (G. japonicus group), photo by J. Boone; C. G. palmatus (G. japonicus group), Quang Binh Province, Vietnam, photo by T. Ziegler; D. G. scientiadventura (G. japonicus group), Quang Binh Province, Vietnam, photo by T. Ziegler." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/278397/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.278398>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A. Male Gekko vertebralis (G. japonicus group), photo by J. Boone; B. G. monarchus (G. monarchus group), Banggai Islands, Indonesia, photo by A. Koch; C. G. ernstkelleri (G. monarchus group), Panay Island, Philippines, photo by M. Gaulke; D. G. mindorensis (G. monarchus group), Cebu Island, Philippines, photo by M. Gaulke." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/278398/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.278396>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Map of East and Southeast Asia and the Indo-Australian Archipelago showing the approximate distribution of (A) the Gekko japonicus, G. petricolus, and G. monarchus groups and G. a t h y m u s and (B) the G. g e c k o, G. p o ro s u s, and G. vittatus groups and G. vietnamensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/278396/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.278394>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Bayesian phylogeny of Gekko, based on nucleotide sequences of the mitochondrial ND 2 gene and nuclear RAG- 1 and PDC genes (2881 bp). Support values (Bayesian pp / ML bootstrap / MP bootstrap) are given at nodes. Species groups proposed herein are indicated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/278394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

